		<Placemark id="02F69AD5743E9267C470">
			<name>Kirishinefteorgsintez Refinery — KINEF</name>
			<description>Refinery: Kirishinefteorgsintez Refinery — KINEF
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Kirishi, Leningrad Oblast, northwestern Russia
Owner: Surgutneftegas, through LLC Production Association Kirishinefteorgsintez
Capacity: About 20 million tonnes per year, equivalent to roughly 400,000 barrels per day; actual processing in 2025 was reported near 18 million tonnes.
Main feedstocks: Russian crude delivered mainly through the domestic pipeline network
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, fuel oil, bitumen, LPG, sulfur, paraffins and petrochemical products
Markets: St. Petersburg and northwestern Russia, with additional product exports through Baltic ports
Recent data: Repeated Ukrainian drone attacks in 2025 and 2026 damaged key units and caused partial or complete shutdowns; a March 2026 strike temporarily halted operations, followed by another major disruption in May.
Strategic role: One of Russia’s two largest refineries and the only major refinery in the country’s northwest, supplying a large share of regional transport fuels
Risks: Drone attacks, unit damage, sanctions, Baltic export disruption, pipeline interruption, fires and prolonged maintenance outages</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>32.04581125495781</longitude>
				<latitude>59.4955761427542</latitude>
				<altitude>16.99807707570836</altitude>
