		<Placemark>
			<name>Mailiao Refinery – Formosa Petrochemical</name>
			<description>Refinery: Mailiao Refinery – Formosa Petrochemical
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Mailiao Township, Yunlin County, Taiwan
Owner: Formosa Petrochemical Corporation, part of the Formosa Plastics Group
Capacity: Approximately 540,000 barrels per day
Main feedstocks: Imported Middle Eastern crude, condensate and other light-to-heavy crude grades
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, LPG, naphtha, marine fuels and petrochemical feedstocks
Markets: Taiwan and export markets across Northeast and Southeast Asia
Recent data: In April 2025, the refinery operated at about 68% of capacity, or roughly 370,000 b/d, because of planned maintenance. In January 2026, Formosa also extended the shutdown of its oldest Mailiao steam cracker because of weak petrochemical margins.
Strategic role: Taiwan’s largest privately owned refinery and a highly integrated refining-petrochemical complex linked to the No. 6 Naphtha Cracker industrial site
Risks: Heavy dependence on imported crude, Strait of Hormuz disruptions, typhoons, port closures, maintenance outages, weak petrochemical margins and regional refining overcapacity</description>
