		<Placemark id="05DDD6E2AF3EAF18E0EF">
			<name>ExxonMobil Singapore Refinery – Jurong Island</name>
			<description>Refinery: ExxonMobil Singapore Refinery – Jurong Island
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Jurong Island, Singapore
Owner: ExxonMobil Asia Pacific, part of ExxonMobil
Capacity: Approximately 592,000 barrels per day of combined nameplate refining capacity
Main feedstocks: Imported Middle Eastern and Asia-Pacific crude oils, condensates and refinery residues
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, marine fuels, LPG, aromatics, waxes and lubricant base stocks
Markets: Singapore and export markets across Northeast Asia, Southeast Asia and the wider Asia-Pacific region
Recent data: The Singapore Resid Upgrade Project started up in 2025, converting about 80,000 b/d of low-value fuel oil into higher-value products, including approximately 50,000 b/d of distillates and 20,000 b/d of lubricant base stocks.
Strategic role: ExxonMobil’s largest integrated refining and petrochemical manufacturing complex, located beside the Strait of Malacca and one of the world’s main fuel-trading and bunkering hubs.
Risks: Dependence on imported crude, Strait of Malacca congestion, South China Sea disruption, refinery outages, weak Asian petrochemical margins and stricter emissions rules</description>
