		<Placemark id="0EBC51FC5A3EB1471A50">
			<name>Reliance Jamnagar Refining Complex</name>
			<description>Refinery: Reliance Jamnagar Refining Complex
Classification: Super-refinery / Mega-refinery
Location: Jamnagar, Gujarat, India
Owner: Reliance Industries Limited
Capacity: Approximately 1.4 million barrels per day across two adjacent refineries, making Jamnagar the world’s largest single-location refining complex.
Main feedstocks: Highly flexible global crude slate, including light, medium, heavy and high-sulfur crude oils
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, naphtha, LPG, marine fuels, petrochemical feedstocks and lubricant-related products
Markets: India and major export markets across Asia, Africa, the Middle East and Europe
Recent data: Reliance’s Oil-to-Chemicals revenue increased 11% year-on-year to about $73.4 billion in FY2024–25, supported by higher volumes and stronger domestic product placement.
Recent operations: In May 2026, Reliance scheduled maintenance on crude and secondary-processing units at its approximately 660,000 b/d export-oriented refinery, with the shutdown expected to last three to four weeks.
Strategic role: One of the world’s most complex and flexible refining-petrochemical hubs, capable of converting lower-quality crude into high-value fuels and chemical feedstocks
Risks: Dependence on imported crude, Strait of Hormuz disruption, sanctions and trade restrictions, refinery-maintenance outages, volatile refining margins, port disruption and cyclone exposure</description>
