		<Placemark id="0B9FB2FB133EB40832C8">
			<name>GS Caltex Yeosu Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: GS Caltex Yeosu Refinery
Classification: Super-refinery / Mega-refinery
Location: Yeosu, Jeollanam-do, South Korea
Owner: GS Caltex, a 50/50 joint venture between GS Energy and Chevron
Capacity: Approximately 800,000 barrels per day of crude-processing capacity
Main feedstocks: Highly diversified imported crude slate, including Middle Eastern, U.S., Asian, European and Australian grades
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, naphtha, LPG, marine fuels, base oils, lubricants and petrochemical feedstocks
Markets: South Korea and export markets across Northeast Asia, Southeast Asia and the wider Pacific region
Recent data: Some crude and downstream units underwent scheduled maintenance in early 2025. In 2026, South Korea also began reviewing a restructuring plan for the wider Yeosu petrochemical complex amid weak margins and regional overcapacity.
Strategic role: One of the world’s largest single-site refineries, with major heavy-oil upgrading capacity that converts lower-value residues into gasoline, diesel and other higher-value products
Risks: Dependence on imported crude, Strait of Hormuz and Malacca disruptions, refinery outages, typhoons, weak Asian petrochemical margins and regional overcapacity</description>
