		<Placemark id="0B015372A33EB40D5613">
			<name>S-OIL Onsan Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: S-OIL Onsan Refinery
Classification: Super-refinery / Mega-refinery
Location: Onsan Industrial Complex, Ulsan, South Korea
Owner: S-OIL Corporation; Saudi Aramco is its controlling shareholder
Capacity: Approximately 669,000 barrels per day across three crude-distillation units
Main feedstocks: Mainly imported Middle Eastern crude, especially Saudi grades, together with other light, medium and sour crudes
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, naphtha, LPG, marine fuels, lubricant base oils, paraxylene and petrochemical feedstocks
Markets: South Korea and export markets across Northeast Asia, Southeast Asia, Europe and the United States
Recent data: The refinery achieved an average crude-distillation utilization rate of about 96% in 2025; scheduled maintenance of the No. 2 crude unit and No. 2 RFCC was planned for 2026.
Strategic role: One of South Korea’s largest integrated refining, lubricant and petrochemical complexes, with major residue-upgrading and paraxylene capacity
Risks: Dependence on imported Middle Eastern crude, Strait of Hormuz disruption, typhoons, unit outages, weak Asian refining margins and regional petrochemical overcapacity</description>
