		<Placemark id="0EB6C96CCE3F337D9842">
			<name>Sinopec Zhenhai Refining &amp; Chemical Complex</name>
			<description>Refinery: Sinopec Zhenhai Refining &amp; Chemical Complex
Classification: Super-refinery / Mega-refinery
Location: Zhenhai District, Ningbo, Zhejiang Province, China
Owner: Sinopec Zhenhai Refining &amp; Chemical Company, part of China Petroleum &amp; Chemical Corporation (Sinopec)
Capacity: About 40 million tonnes per year, equivalent to roughly 800,000 barrels per day, across the integrated refining and chemical base
Main feedstocks: Imported Middle Eastern, Russian, African and other global crude grades, together with condensates and intermediate feedstocks
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, LPG, naphtha, aromatics, ethylene, plastics and other petrochemical products
Markets: Primarily eastern China, especially the Yangtze River Delta, with selected refined-product and petrochemical exports across Asia
Recent data: Sinopec reported that Zhenhai became its first 40-million-tonne-per-year refining and chemical base. In March 2026, the complex reduced utilization at its two steam crackers to roughly 70–80% amid Middle Eastern supply disruptions and weaker petrochemical economics.
Strategic role: One of China’s largest and most integrated refining-petrochemical hubs, supplying fuels and chemical feedstocks to the highly industrialized Yangtze River Delta
Risks: Dependence on imported crude, Strait of Hormuz and Malacca disruptions, Ningbo port congestion, typhoons, refinery or cracker outages, weak Asian petrochemical margins and Chinese fuel-export restrictions</description>
