		<Placemark id="040E9977C63FCC60F669">
			<name>Bayernoil Refinery – Neustadt/Vohburg</name>
			<description>Refinery: Bayernoil Refinery – Neustadt/Vohburg
Classification: Large refinery — not a mega-refinery
Location: Neustadt an der Donau and Vohburg, Bavaria, Germany
Owner: Joint venture; majority-owned by VARO Energy, with additional stakes held by Eni and Rosneft Deutschland under German trusteeship arrangements
Capacity: Up to 10 million tonnes per year, equivalent to roughly 200,000–210,000 b/d for the two-site refinery system
Main feedstocks: Imported crude delivered through the Transalpine Pipeline system and regional pipeline connections
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, heating oil, jet fuel components, LPG and bitumen
Markets: Bavaria and northern Austria, including regional road-fuel, aviation and industrial demand
Recent data: A major fire occurred at the Neustadt site in January 2025, injuring two people and temporarily disrupting operations; the company’s 2025 environmental report confirms continued operation of the two-site complex
Strategic role: Bavaria’s largest refining company and an important inland fuel supplier for southern Germany and Austria
Risks: Pipeline-supply disruption, industrial fires and unit outages, high European energy and carbon costs, declining regional fuel demand and Rhine/Alpine logistics constraints</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>11.7617685</longitude>
				<latitude>48.7842741</latitude>
