		<Placemark>
			<name>Sonatrach Skikda Refinery &amp; Petrochemical Complex</name>
			<description>Refinery: Sonatrach Skikda Refinery — RA1K
Classification: Mega-refinery
Location: Skikda Industrial Zone, Skikda Province, northeastern Algeria, on the Mediterranean coast
Owner/Operator: Sonatrach
Capacity: Approximately 16.5 million tonnes of crude oil per year, equivalent to roughly 320,000–335,000 barrels per day
Main feedstocks: Primarily Algerian crude oil, especially light Saharan grades transported from inland producing regions through the national pipeline network
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, LPG, naphtha, fuel oil, bitumen, aromatics, benzene, xylene and other refinery and petrochemical feedstocks
Markets: Algeria’s domestic fuel market and export markets in Europe, the Mediterranean and other international destinations
Configuration: Large integrated refining and petrochemical complex with crude distillation, reforming, hydrotreating, aromatics production and supporting utility and storage systems
Operating history: Commissioned in 1980 and extensively modernized during a major rehabilitation completed around 2013
Recent development: Sonatrach has been developing additional fuel-oil conversion and hydrocracking capacity to increase production of higher-value gasoline and diesel and reduce lower-value fuel-oil output
Strategic role: Algeria’s largest refinery and one of Africa’s largest refining sites, supplying a substantial share of national petroleum-product demand while supporting exports through the adjacent Skikda hydrocarbon port
Risks: Refinery-unit outages, fires, ageing infrastructure, pipeline interruption, Mediterranean shipping disruption, industrial accidents and delays to conversion projects</description>
