		<name>Refineries</name>
		<Placemark id="0AB8DCAC2D4013E81D84">
			<name>Atyrau Oil Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Atyrau Oil Refinery
Location: Atyrau, western Kazakhstan
Owner: KazMunayGas, which owns 99% of the refinery
Capacity: 5.5 million tonnes per year, equivalent to roughly 105,000–115,000 barrels per day depending on the crude processed
Main feedstocks: Primarily Kazakh crude from western Kazakhstan, including nearby Caspian-producing regions
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, LPG, vacuum gasoil, fuel oil, petroleum coke and petrochemical feedstocks
Markets: Mainly Kazakhstan’s domestic market, particularly western and central regions
Recent data: A comprehensive modernization programme is running from 2023 to 2027 to improve reliability, upgrade key units and increase the yield of light refined products.
Strategic role: One of Kazakhstan’s three principal refineries and a key supplier of fuels to the country’s oil-producing western region
Risks: Aging equipment, unplanned unit outages, dependence on domestic pipeline supply, power or utility disruptions, environmental constraints and inland logistics limitations</description>
