		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="05A97C7E0C3F23806BD3">
			<name>Rosneft Tuapse Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Rosneft Tuapse Refinery
Location: Tuapse, Krasnodar Krai, Russia, on the Black Sea coast
Owner: Rosneft
Capacity: Approximately 12 million tonnes per year, equivalent to about 240,000 barrels per day
Main feedstocks: Russian crude supplied through the domestic pipeline and rail network
Main products: Diesel, naphtha, fuel oil, LPG, sulfur and other export-oriented petroleum products
Markets: Mainly international export markets through the adjacent Tuapse marine terminal, particularly Mediterranean and Black Sea destinations
Recent data: Operations were halted after a drone attack in April 2026. A further strike later that month caused a major fire; the site has remained highly exposed to repeated attacks and operational disruptions.
Strategic role: Major export-oriented Black Sea refinery directly linked to the Tuapse petroleum-products terminal, which has annual handling capacity of about 10.2 million tonnes.
Risks: Drone and missile attacks, Black Sea security, sanctions, terminal shutdowns, pipeline or rail disruption, fires, refinery outages and restricted access to international markets</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>39.0984808</longitude>
				<latitude>44.1016933</latitude>
				<altitude>17.35736417100845</altitude>
