		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="0D693674733F39E868C4">
			<name>South Refineries Company – Basra Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: South Refineries Company – Basra Refinery
Classification: Large refinery — not a mega-refinery
Location: Shuaiba industrial area, Basra Governorate, southern Iraq
Owner/Operator: South Refineries Company, a state-owned company under the Iraqi Ministry of Oil
Capacity: Approximately 210,000 barrels per day
Main feedstocks: Iraqi crude oil, mainly supplied from southern oil fields around Basra
Main products: LPG, gasoline, kerosene, jet fuel, diesel/gas oil, fuel oil, marine fuel, base oils and other petroleum derivatives
Markets: Primarily southern Iraq and the national Iraqi domestic market
Recent development: The refinery has undergone a major modernization program, including new conversion and fuel-quality units designed to increase production of gasoline and other higher-value products. Commercial operation of upgraded facilities was expected from late 2025 onward.
Strategic role: One of Iraq’s largest refining sites and the principal supplier of refined fuels to Basra and southern Iraq
Risks: Power outages, ageing infrastructure, operational interruptions, regional security risks, crude-supply disruptions and delays in modernization projects</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>47.66685409999999</longitude>
				<latitude>30.45065369999999</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
