		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="010A05BCD03F39FB8517">
			<name>North Refineries Company – Haditha Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: North Refineries Company – Haditha Refinery
Classification: Small conventional refinery / expansion project
Location: Haditha, Al-Anbar Governorate, western Iraq, near the Euphrates River
Owner/Operator: North Refineries Company (NRC), a state-owned company under the Iraqi Ministry of Oil
Existing capacity: Historically around 16,000 barrels per day
Expansion: A new 20,000 b/d refining unit was launched to raise total capacity to approximately 36,000 b/d. Iraqi authorities have also referred to a broader Haditha development project targeting up to 70,000 b/d, involving technology and engineering support from Honeywell UOP.
Main feedstocks: Iraqi crude supplied through the national pipeline and storage system
Main products: Gasoline, diesel/gas oil, kerosene, naphtha, fuel oil and LPG-related streams
Markets: Primarily Al-Anbar Governorate and western Iraq’s domestic fuel market
Strategic role: Provides locally refined fuels to western Iraq, an area located far from the country’s principal refining centres. Its importance could increase with the proposed Basra–Haditha crude pipeline, which is intended to strengthen domestic crude transportation and refining supply.
Risks: Uncertain expansion timetable, differences between existing and planned capacity, pipeline dependency, ageing infrastructure, electricity interruptions, security risks and limited publicly available operating data</description>
