		<Placemark id="017FD5AE0A3F39FE58C4">
			<name>Midland Refineries Company – Samawah Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Midland Refineries Company – Samawah Refinery
Classification: Small conventional refinery
Location: Samawah, Al-Muthanna Governorate, southern Iraq
Owner/Operator: Midland Refineries Company (MRC), under the Iraqi Ministry of Oil
Current capacity: Approximately 30,000 barrels per day. This figure is confirmed in Midland Refineries Company documentation and recent Iraqi government statements.
Main feedstocks: Iraqi crude oil supplied through the national crude-distribution and pipeline network
Main products: Gasoline, kerosene, diesel/gas oil, fuel oil and other basic petroleum products
Markets: Mainly Al-Muthanna Governorate and surrounding areas of southern and central Iraq
Configuration: Relatively simple refinery focused on supplying the regional domestic market, with limited upgrading and conversion capacity
Planned development: Iraq has also promoted a separate 70,000 b/d Al-Samawah investment refinery project. This remains a development opportunity and should not be confused with the existing 30,000 b/d refinery.
Strategic role: Provides locally refined fuels to Al-Muthanna and reduces the need to transport all petroleum products from larger refining centres such as Basra, Karbala and Baghdad
Risks: Ageing equipment, limited conversion capacity, power interruptions, maintenance constraints, pipeline dependence and uncertainty surrounding the proposed expansion project</description>
