		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="06268871DE3F39FF2AB9">
			<name>South Refineries Company – Dhi Qar Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: South Refineries Company – Dhi Qar Refinery
Alternative name: Nasiriyah Refinery
Classification: Small conventional refinery
Location: Dhi Qar Governorate, near Nasiriyah, southern Iraq
Owner/Operator: South Refineries Company, under the Iraqi Ministry of Oil
Current capacity: Approximately 30,000 barrels per day
Configuration: Three primary refining units of about 10,000 b/d each, together with an asphalt unit rated at approximately 500 tonnes per day
Operating history: The first units were established in 1980–1981, while commercial production began in 1984.
Main feedstocks: Iraqi crude oil supplied from producing fields in southern Iraq through the national petroleum network
Main products: Gasoline components, diesel/gas oil, kerosene, fuel oil, naphtha and asphalt/bitumen
Markets: Primarily Dhi Qar Governorate, Nasiriyah and neighbouring areas of southern Iraq
Strategic role: Provides regional fuel and asphalt production, reducing the need to transport all petroleum products from the larger Basra refining complex
Risks: Ageing equipment, low conversion complexity, electricity interruptions, maintenance constraints, limited operating transparency and dependence on regional crude-supply infrastructure</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>46.2199375</longitude>
				<latitude>30.9943125</latitude>
