				<altitudeMode>relativeToGround</altitudeMode>
				<coordinates>35.9594271,35.2162342,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="06BC5073B93F3A187DE1">
			<name>Midland Refineries Company – Karbala Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Karbala Refinery
Classification: Conventional refinery — just below the large-refinery threshold
Location: Approximately 40 km southwest of Karbala city, Karbala Governorate, Iraq
Owner: Iraqi Ministry of Oil
Operator: Midland Refineries Company (MRC); operations and maintenance support has also been contracted to Rowwad Al-Qimmah Company
Capacity: 140,000 barrels per day
Main feedstocks: Iraqi crude oil supplied mainly from southern Iraq through the national pipeline network
Main products: LPG, gasoline, kerosene, jet fuel, diesel, heavy gas oil, fuel oil, bitumen and sulfur
Fuel quality: Designed to produce relatively low-sulfur fuels meeting modern European-type specifications
Configuration: Modern conversion refinery with catalytic cracking, hydrotreating, reforming, isomerization and supporting hydrogen and sulfur-recovery units
Power infrastructure: Integrated power plant of approximately 200 MW, partly supporting refinery operations and the national electricity system
Markets: Primarily Iraq’s domestic market, particularly central and southern regions
Operating status: Inaugurated in April 2023 and subsequently ramped up toward its nominal capacity. Industry reporting placed throughput around 115,000 b/d in August 2025, although Iraqi officials later reported operation at full capacity.
Strategic role: One of Iraq’s newest and most technologically advanced refineries, built to reduce imports of gasoline, diesel and other refined products
Risks: Pipeline disruption, shortages of crude or utilities, maintenance and commissioning problems, security threats, operational-contract issues and differences between nominal capacity and actual throughput</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>44.07990739999999</longitude>
				<latitude>32.3707476</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
				<heading>0</heading>
