			<Point>
				<altitudeMode>relativeToGround</altitudeMode>
				<coordinates>44.0799074,32.3707476,0</coordinates>
			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark id="025B0D49523F4B68D7B2">
			<name>Dung Quat Oil Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Dung Quat Oil Refinery
Classification: Conventional refinery, close to the large-refinery threshold
Location: Dung Quat Economic Zone, Quang Ngai Province, Vietnam
Owner: Operated by Binh Son Refining and Petrochemical JSC (BSR), majority-owned by Petrovietnam
Capacity: 148,000 barrels per day nominal; an expansion project is intended to raise capacity to 171,000 b/d
Main feedstocks: Traditionally Vietnamese sweet crude, especially Bach Ho, increasingly blended with imported grades such as Murban and other Asian or Middle Eastern crudes
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, LPG, polypropylene, fuel oil and sulfur products
Markets: Primarily Vietnam’s domestic fuel market, with selected petrochemical and by-product exports
Recent data: The refinery operated at about 123.5% of adjusted capacity in Q1 2026. In 2025, BSR also launched sulfur pastilles and continued preparations for a nearly $1.5 billion expansion.
Strategic role: Vietnam’s first refinery and a major contributor to national fuel security, reducing dependence on imported refined products
Risks: Dependence on domestic crude availability, exposure to imported-crude freight and Strait of Hormuz disruptions, typhoons, refinery outages and delays to the expansion project</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>108.8220273</longitude>
				<latitude>15.3540319</latitude>
				<altitude>0</altitude>
