		<Placemark id="0429F90FA83F7ED8A192">
			<name>TotalEnergies Donges Refinery – Nantes–Saint-Nazaire</name>
			<description>Refinery: TotalEnergies Donges Refinery
Classification: Large refinery — not a mega-refinery
Location: Donges, Loire-Atlantique, near Saint-Nazaire, France — postal code 44480
Owner/Operator: TotalEnergies Raffinage France
Capacity: Approximately 230,000 barrels per day
Main feedstocks: Imported crude oils delivered through the deep-water facilities and petroleum terminals of the Port of Nantes–Saint-Nazaire
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, LPG, heating oil, marine fuels, bitumen and intermediate refinery products
Markets: Western France, the Paris region and Atlantic European markets
Configuration: Large conversion refinery with around 20 production units, storage infrastructure and connections to regional product-distribution networks.
Recent development: The Horizon modernization project, representing roughly €400 million of investment, was designed to improve the production of low-sulfur fuels and the refinery’s competitiveness. The site underwent a major turnaround in 2026, followed by the progressive restart of its units in June.
Strategic role: One of TotalEnergies’ three operating refineries in metropolitan France and a key fuel supplier for western France.
Risks: Atlantic marine-logistics disruption, refinery outages, labour action, fires, high European energy and carbon costs, environmental constraints and dependence on regional petroleum-product demand</description>
