		<Placemark>
			<name>Suncor Montreal Refinery</name>
			<description>Refinery: Suncor Montréal Refinery
Classification: Conventional refinery — not a large or mega-refinery
Location: Montréal-Est, Quebec, Canada
Owner/Operator: Suncor Energy
Capacity: Approximately 137,000 barrels per day
Crude storage capacity: About 1.4 billion litres
Main feedstocks: Primarily Canadian crude oils, including Western Canadian grades delivered through the Enbridge Line 9 pipeline system; the refinery can also access imported crude through eastern Canadian marine and pipeline infrastructure.
Main products: Gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, heating oil, asphalt, heavy fuel oil, solvents, petrochemical feedstocks and lubricant feedstocks
Markets: Quebec, Ontario and other eastern Canadian markets
Integration: The refinery is connected to Montréal’s storage, terminal, pipeline and marine logistics network and includes an associated sulphur-processing facility
Recent performance: Suncor’s company-wide refinery throughput reached about 498,000 b/d in Q1 2026, with utilization of approximately 97%; this figure covers Suncor’s entire refining system rather than Montréal alone.
Strategic role: One of Quebec’s two principal refineries and a key supplier of transport fuels and asphalt to eastern Canada
Risks: Enbridge Line 9 disruption, marine-logistics constraints, refinery outages, severe winter weather, environmental regulation, carbon costs and dependence on eastern Canadian fuel demand</description>
