		<Placemark id="0ABF44347B3FDB9E58EA">
			<name>Gunvor Energy Rotterdam</name>
			<description>Refinery: Gunvor Energy Rotterdam
Location: Europoort, Rotterdam, Netherlands
Owner: Gunvor Group
Nominal capacity: About 75,000 barrels per day
Current status: The crude-distillation units were permanently closed in 2021, so the site no longer operates as a conventional full crude refinery. Gunvor later retained product-processing and terminal activities, but announced plans in 2025 to mothball the Europoort terminal operations.
Main feedstocks: Historically crude oil; more recently intermediate products and finished petroleum products
Main products: LPG, naphtha, gasoline, gasoil and other intermediate or finished products
Markets: Rotterdam and Northwest European product markets
Recent data: Gunvor temporarily halted refinery operations in late 2024 because suitable feedstock was not commercially viable, and in July 2025 announced plans to suspend terminal activities.
Transition plans: The site has been positioned for gradual conversion toward lower-carbon energy and sustainable-fuel activities rather than traditional crude refining.
Strategic role: Historically a small Rotterdam refinery and terminal; today better viewed as an energy-transition and storage site
Risks: Permanent loss of refining activity, terminal mothballing, weak European margins, feedstock availability, transition-project delays and regulatory uncertainty</description>
