		<Placemark>
			<name>Skikda Oil Terminal</name>
			<description>Facility: Skikda Hydrocarbon Storage &amp; Tank Farm Complex
Classification: Major integrated crude-oil, refined-products, LNG and petrochemical storage complex
Location: Skikda Industrial Zone, between the RA1K refinery, LNG facilities and Port El Djedid, Algeria
Owner/Operators: Mainly Sonatrach and affiliated refinery, liquefaction, pipeline and petrochemical divisions
Main commodities: Crude oil, condensate, gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, naphtha, fuel oil, LPG, LNG feedstocks, aromatics and intermediate petroleum products
Main functions: Receipt, segregation, buffer storage, blending, refinery feed management and preparation of export cargoes
Infrastructure: Multiple large atmospheric tanks, smaller product tanks, pressurized LPG storage, pipeline manifolds, pumping stations and connections to refinery units and marine loading berths
Connected facilities: RA1K crude refinery, RA2K condensate refinery, GL1K LNG complex, petrochemical plants, inland pipeline systems and the Skikda hydrocarbon port
Strategic role: Provides operational flexibility between incoming pipeline flows, refinery production, domestic distribution and maritime exports
Storage capacity: A single consolidated public figure for all oil-product tank farms visible in the image is not clearly published. The LNG complex alone has three tanks with combined capacity of 246,000 m³.
Risks: Tank fires, vapour release, product contamination, spills, overfilling, pipeline failures and cascading incidents within the densely integrated industrial zone</description>
