		<Placemark>
			<name>Yeosu–Gwangyang Industrial Port – Refining &amp; Chemical Hub</name>
			<description>Hub: Yeosu–Gwangyang Industrial Port – Refining, Petrochemical &amp; Bulk Logistics Hub
Classification: Major refining, petrochemical, bulk-industrial and maritime logistics hub
Location: Jeollanam-do, southern coast of South Korea
Owner/Operator: Yeosu Gwangyang Port Authority; industrial assets are operated by companies including GS Caltex, petrochemical producers and steel operators
Main commodities: Crude oil, gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, naphtha, LPG, petrochemicals, chemicals, LNG, steel-related cargoes, coal, ore and containers
Main facilities: Large crude and product berths, refinery terminals, petrochemical jetties, tank farms, bulk terminals, industrial estates and logistics infrastructure
Refining cluster: Anchored by the GS Caltex Yeosu Refinery, one of the largest refining complexes in Asia
Industrial integration: Closely linked with petrochemical production, bulk materials, power generation, steel logistics and export-oriented manufacturing
Export role: Major outlet for fuels, naphtha, aromatics and petrochemical derivatives into Asian markets
Connectivity: Excellent coastal-shipping access and strong inland connections to South Korea’s industrial base
Main markets: South Korea, Northeast Asia and Southeast Asia
Energy-transition role: Growing attention to hydrogen, ammonia, petrochemical restructuring, low-carbon fuels and cleaner industrial operations
Strategic role: One of South Korea’s core energy and industrial port systems, combining fuel production, chemicals and heavy-industry logistics in one integrated coastal hub
Risks: Imported-crude dependence, typhoons, industrial accidents, refinery outages, petrochemical oversupply, weak margins and regional trade disruptions</description>
