		<Placemark>
			<name>Jamnagar–Sikka Global Refining &amp; Export Hub</name>
			<description>Hub: Jamnagar–Sikka Energy, Refining &amp; Maritime Logistics Hub
Classification: Global super-refining, crude-import, product-export and industrial port hub
Location: Jamnagar district, Gujarat, western India, on the Gulf of Kutch
Owner/Operator: Main industrial assets operated by Reliance Industries; associated port and terminal infrastructure includes Sikka and nearby marine facilities
Main commodities: Crude oil, gasoline, diesel, jet fuel, naphtha, LPG, petcoke, marine fuels, petrochemical feedstocks and other refined products
Main facilities: Very large crude-import terminals, refinery jetties, product-export berths, tank farms, petrochemical units, utilities and supporting industrial infrastructure
Refining cluster: Centred on the Reliance Jamnagar Refining Complex, the world’s largest single-location refining complex, with around 1.4 million b/d of capacity across two refineries
Crude-import role: Receives a highly diversified global crude slate, including light, medium, heavy and sour grades
Export role: One of the world’s largest export centres for refined petroleum products, shipping to Asia, Africa, Europe and the Middle East
Connectivity: Excellent marine access, extensive storage and pipeline connections inside the industrial complex, and direct integration with petrochemical and utility systems
Main markets: India, Europe, Africa, Asia and global spot and contract product markets
Energy-transition role: Growing interest in renewable fuels, hydrogen, downstream decarbonization and wider low-carbon industrial investments by Reliance
Strategic role: One of the most significant refining and export hubs in the world, especially for middle distillates and globally traded clean products
Risks: Dependence on imported crude, Gulf shipping disruptions, cyclones, refinery maintenance outages, environmental constraints and volatile global refining margins</description>
