			</Point>
		</Placemark>
		<Placemark>
			<name>Port of Texas City</name>
			<description>Hub: Port of Texas City – Crude Import, Refining &amp; Storage Hub
Classification: Crude-oil import, refinery-supply, storage and petrochemical port
Location: Texas City, on the western side of Galveston Bay near the entrance to the Houston Ship Channel
Owner/Operator: Operated through the Texas City Terminal Railway Company; refinery and crude-terminal facilities are privately operated
Main commodities: Crude oil, refinery feedstocks, gasoline, diesel and other petroleum and petrochemical cargoes
Main facilities: Crude and product docks, storage tanks, refinery terminals, railway infrastructure and connections to the Seaway crude system
Refining cluster: Centred on Marathon Petroleum’s Galveston Bay refinery and the Valero Texas City refinery. Marathon’s integrated Galveston Bay complex has crude-processing capacity of approximately 631,000 barrels per calendar day.
Crude flows: Receives crude by tanker and pipeline for processing in Texas City and Houston-area refineries. Seaway infrastructure connects the port with Cushing and regional storage and refinery systems
Connectivity: Pipeline links to Cushing, Houston-area terminals and local refineries; rail connections through the Texas City Terminal Railway; marine access through Galveston Bay
Main markets: Primarily Texas City and Houston-area refineries rather than international crude buyers
Bunkering role: Limited; the port’s principal marine-energy function is receiving crude and moving refined products
Energy-transition role: Focused mainly on improving refinery efficiency and processing flexibility rather than developing a separate low-carbon fuel-trading hub
Strategic role: A major crude-receiving and refinery-feed port. The port identifies crude oil among its principal imports and exports and accommodates Aframax and Suezmax petroleum tankers.
Risks: Hurricanes, storm surge, refinery accidents, ship-channel disruption, oil spills, ageing industrial infrastructure and concentration around a small number of large refineries</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>-94.90908642676216</longitude>
