	<Folder>
		<name>Renewable Fuels &amp; Low-Carbon Production Sites</name>
		<Placemark id="0E467C7C173FCEB24E88">
			<name>VAROPreem Lysekil Refinery &amp; Renewable Fuels Hub</name>
			<description>Refinery: VAROPreem Lysekil Refinery &amp; Renewable Fuels Hub
Classification: Large refinery and renewable-fuels production site
Location: Lysekil, Västra Götaland County, Sweden
Owner: VAROPreem
Capacity: Approximately 220,000 barrels per day of conventional refining capacity
Renewable capacity: Up to 900,000 m³/year from the upgraded Synsat unit; total Lysekil renewable capacity exceeds 1 million m³/year
Main feedstocks: Imported crude oils and renewable raw materials such as tall oil, used cooking oils, animal fats and pyrolysis oils
Main products: Diesel, gasoline, LPG, HVO renewable diesel and other co-processed renewable fuels
Markets: Sweden, Norway and other Northwest European markets
Recent data: The Synsat upgrade entered service in 2025, allowing up to 40% renewable material to be co-processed with diesel
Strategic role: Major Nordic refinery and large-scale renewable-fuels hub supporting the decarbonisation of road, marine, aviation and industrial transport
Risks: Seaborne-feedstock dependence, refinery outages, North Sea weather, high energy and carbon costs, and uncertainty over future fuel demand</description>
			<LookAt>
				<longitude>11.4172029</longitude>
				<latitude>58.3484121</latitude>
