		<Placemark id="0A981C3A6A3F2D3C6D14">
			<name>Kirkuk–Ceyhan Oil Pipeline</name>
			<description><![CDATA[<div style="font-family:Arial,sans-serif;font-size:13px;line-height:1.5"><b>⚠️ Status: NOT operational.</b><br>The Kirkuk–Ceyhan crude pipeline (Iraq → Turkey) is currently offline for political reasons — the dispute between Baghdad (federal government) and Erbil (Kurdistan Regional Government) over control of northern Iraqi crude exports.<br><b>Route:</b> Kirkuk (Iraq) → Ceyhan (Turkey, Mediterranean export terminal)<br><b>Significance:</b> When operational, a key outlet for northern Iraqi/Kurdish crude to the Mediterranean.</div>]]></description>
