		<name>Pipelines refined products</name>
		<Placemark id="ADDRRB00000000000001">
			<name>Rostock–Böhlen product pipeline (RRB)</name>
			<description><![CDATA[Classification: Refined products / petrochemical feedstock pipeline (Rohstoffpipeline Rostock–Böhlen, RRB)<br>Route: Rostock oil port (GÖR terminal) → Leuna → Dow Böhlen cracker complex, ~430 km, up to 16-inch; in service since 1997<br>Owner/Operator: Dow Olefinverbund (Dow Chemical)<br>Handles: Naphtha, pyrolysis gasoline and condensate; also approved for pentane, benzene, crude oil (Rostock to Leuna) and C3+ LPG<br>Connectivity: Feeds the Böhlen naphtha cracker (ethylene and propylene for the Schkopau and Leuna plants); part of Dow's ~1,300 km Central German pipeline network<br>Recent data: Dow has applied to extend the approved cargo list to bio-based and recycled feedstocks (HVO-type and plastic-waste-derived) — an energy-transition signal<br>Strategic role: The petrochemical twin of the Schwedt crude line — the second artery that makes Rostock the seaborne supply gateway for eastern Germany's refining and chemical industry<br>Risks: Single-line dependence for the Böhlen cracker's feedstock supply; cracker margin exposure]]></description>
			<styleUrl>#msn_icon?color=1976d2&amp;id=2000&amp;scale=400</styleUrl>
