		<Placemark id="0DBB3F106040213031C4">
			<name>Ekofisk crude route</name>
			<description>Crude: Ekofisk Blend
API: ~38.8°
Sulfur: ~0.20–0.21%
Type: Light, sweet North Sea crude
Origin: Greater Ekofisk Area, Norwegian North Sea; transported through the 354 km Norpipe system to the Teesside Oil Terminal, United Kingdom
Markets: Mainly Northwest European refiners, including the United Kingdom, the Netherlands, Germany and France
Used for: Gasoline, naphtha, jet fuel, diesel, gasoil and petrochemical feedstocks
Pricing: One of the BFOET grades used in the Dated Brent benchmark; traded at a variable differential according to supply, refinery demand and freight
Vessels: Typically Aframax or Suezmax tankers loaded at the Teesside terminal
Transit: Around 1–3 days from Teesside to Rotterdam
Risks: North Sea weather, Norpipe or terminal outages, loading delays and congestion in the English Channel and Rotterdam approaches</description>
