		<Placemark>
			<name>Sakhalin Blend route</name>
			<description>Crude: Sakhalin Blend
API: ~45.5°
Sulfur: ~0.16%
Type: Ultra-light, sweet crude
Origin: Sakhalin-2 fields, Russian Far East; exported from Prigorodnoye Terminal
Main market: Japan, with additional sales to China and other Asia-Pacific refiners
Used for: Naphtha, gasoline, jet fuel, diesel and petrochemical feedstocks
Pricing: Usually assessed against Dubai/Oman or regional Asia-Pacific light-crude benchmarks
Vessels: Typically loaded on Aframax tankers at Prigorodnoye
Transit: Around 4–7 days to northern Japan, depending on destination and weather
Risks: Ice, severe winter weather, sanctions, payment restrictions and navigation constraints around Sakhalin and northern Japan</description>
